The Seven Masters: Before they were geniuses.
They were men who sought their own language.

Van Gogh left 900 works in ten years and then left;
His star still revolves today.

Klimt hid love and death under gold leaf;
Munch breathed out the cries of his lost loved ones all his life.

Matisse guarded the joy of color even in the midst of war;
Chagall flies in the sky with her lover.

Frida faces the broken body with a gaze;
Lichtenstein questioned the world with his one-panel comics.

They question, they destroy, they rebuild.
Seven worlds. It's your turn to answer.

